  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $f(n;t)$ be minimal such that if a $t$-uniform hypergraph on $n$ vertices contains at least $f(n;t)$ edges then there must be four edges $A,B,C,D$ such that\\[A\\cup B= C\\cup D\\]and\\[A\\cap B=C\\cap D=\\emptyset.\\]Estimate $f(n;t)$ - in particular, is it true that for $t\\geq 3$\\[f(n;t)=(1+o(1))\\binom{n}{t-1}?\\]",
